
h2. OpenWFEru source code

Since April 2008, the source code of OpenWFEru is hosted at "http://github.com/jmettraux/ruote":http://github.com/jmettraux/ruote

If the "git":http://git.or.cz/ tools are available on your system, you can check out (clone) the source of OpenWFEru by doing :

<pre>
    git clone git://github.com/jmettraux/ruote.git
</pre>

That will check out OpenWFEru's source under a <tt>ruote/</tt> directory.

If you're a github user, it's easy for you to fork OpenWFEru there and play with your version.

The developer mailing list for OpenWFE is at "http://groups.google.com/group/openwferu-dev":http://groups.google.com/group/openwferu-dev


h3. other OpenWFEru components

They are all at "http://github.com/jmettraux":http://github.com/jmettraux

The highlights are :

* "Ruote-web":http://github.com/jmettraux/ruote-web (ex-"Densha") : a Ruby on Rails web application wrapping the OpenWFEru ruote engine. ("online demo":http://difference.openwfe.org:3000)

* "Ruote-rest":http://github.com/jmettraux/ruote-rest : A "Sinatra":http://sinatrarb.com based RESTful BPM / workflow service
